# Kotlin Conventions

## Immutability First
```kotlin
// ❌ BAD
var rides = mutableListOf<Ride>()

// ✅ GOOD — immutable state, replace on update
val rides: List<Ride> = emptyList()
```
Prefer `val` over `var`. Use `data class` for models; never mutate them — copy instead.

## Null Safety
```kotlin
// ❌ BAD — force unwrap
val name = user!!.name

// ✅ GOOD
val name = user?.name ?: "Unknown"
```
Never use `!!` outside of tests. Use `?.let`, `?: return`, or `requireNotNull` with a message.

## Sealed Classes for State & Events
```kotlin
sealed class UiState {
    object Loading : UiState()
    data class Success(val rides: List<Ride>) : UiState()
    data class Error(val message: String) : UiState()
}
```

## Coroutines
- Use `viewModelScope` in ViewModels, `lifecycleScope` in Activity/Fragment
- Never launch on `Dispatchers.Main` for IO — use `Dispatchers.IO` in the data layer
- Use `Flow` for streams, `suspend` for one-shot operations

## Extension Functions
Use extension functions for reusable UI helpers and mappers:
```kotlin
fun Ride.toUiModel(): RideUiModel = RideUiModel(id = id, routeSummary = "$origin → $destination")
```

## No Magic Numbers
```kotlin
// ❌ BAD
if (remainingQuota < 5) showWarning()

// ✅ GOOD
const val QUOTA_WARNING_THRESHOLD = 5
if (remainingQuota < QUOTA_WARNING_THRESHOLD) showWarning()
```
